  ib jerry check-address [flags]

DESCRIPTION
  Anonymous geofence feasibility probe (POST /api/pumppuRequests/checkAddress): which provider varikot cover an address. The single best tool for diagnosing 'no offers'. --address is required (the \`osoite\` body field); if --lat/--lng/--place-id are all supplied the server trusts them instead of re-geocoding. Not a mutation, so no write-safety flags. Rate-limited 10/min per IP. The \`providers\` array is only included when the token is a developer/admin.
  Timezone: dates interpreted in active company timezone (Europe/Helsinki).

FLAGS
  --address STRING    Street address to check (REQUIRED; sent as \`osoite\`)
  --lat NUMBER    Latitude (trusted only with --lng + --place-id)
  --lng NUMBER    Longitude (trusted only with --lat + --place-id)
  --place-id STRING    Google placeId (lets the server trust client coords)
  --formatted-address STRING    Google formatted address

GLOBAL FLAGS
  --endpoint URL  --request-id ID  --quiet  --verbose  --pretty  --json

OUTPUT (JSON, stdout)
  { geocoded: boolean, deliverable?: boolean, lat?, lng?, placeId?, formattedAddress?, providerCount?, nearestVarikkoKm?, providers?: [{ asiakasId, asiakasNimi, distanceKm }] }

ERRORS (stderr, exit non-zero)
  400  osoite missing         → pass --address
  429  Rate limit (10/min/IP) → wait and retry
  500  Backend error          → retry with --verbose

EXAMPLES
  ib jerry check-address --address 'Mannerheimintie 1, Helsinki'
  ib jerry check-address --address 'Hämeenkatu 1, Tampere' --lat 61.498 --lng 23.761 --place-id ChIJxxxx
"
`;

exports[`Help snapshots — contract stability > help for ib jerry counts matches snapshot 1`] = `
"USAGE
  ib jerry counts [flags]

DESCRIPTION
  Lifecycle counts. Default --mine returns the customer view (GET /api/pumppuRequests/mine/counts: draft/open/pending_verification/accepted/cancelled/expired/no_supply). --provider returns the provider badge counts (GET /api/pumppuRequests/provider-counts: avoimet/tarjotut/voitetut/voitetutActionRequired/paattyneet) and requires a provider company.
  Permissions: requires --provider: provider company (isPumppuToimittaja).
  Timezone: dates interpreted in active company timezone (Europe/Helsinki).

FLAGS
  --provider BOOLEAN    Provider badge counts (provider role)
  --mine BOOLEAN    Customer counts (default)

GLOBAL FLAGS
  --endpoint URL  --request-id ID  --quiet  --verbose  --pretty  --json

OUTPUT (JSON, stdout)
  --mine: { draft, open, pending_verification, accepted, cancelled, expired, no_supply } | --provider: { avoimet, tarjotut, voitetut, voitetutActionRequired, paattyneet }

ERRORS (stderr, exit non-zero)
  403  Not a provider (for --provider) → switch to a provider company, or use --mine
  401  Token expired          → ib auth refresh
  500  Backend error          → retry with --verbose

EXAMPLES
  ib jerry counts
  ib jerry counts --provider
"
`;

exports[`Help snapshots — contract stability > help for ib jerry provider-settings get matches snapshot 1`] = `
"USAGE
  ib jerry provider-settings get [flags]

DESCRIPTION
  Read a provider company's BetoniJerry settings — contact person, opening hours, company description, maintainsOrderInfo (GET /api/jerry-provider-settings). Defaults to the caller's own company; --asiakas targets another company you have edit rights on. Returns defaults when no row exists yet.
  Permissions: requires edit-tier on the target company (tarjousAdmin / company admin).
  Timezone: dates interpreted in active company timezone (Europe/Helsinki).

FLAGS
  --asiakas NUMBER    Target company asiakasId (default: your own)

GLOBAL FLAGS
  --endpoint URL  --request-id ID  --quiet  --verbose  --pretty  --json

OUTPUT (JSON, stdout)
  { asiakasId, jerryPersonId, jerryPersonName, jerryPersonPhone, openingHours, companyDescription, maintainsOrderInfo }

ERRORS (stderr, exit non-zero)
  403  No edit rights on company → use a tarjousAdmin/admin token for that company
  401  Token expired          → ib auth refresh
  500  Backend error          → retry with --verbose

EXAMPLES
  ib jerry provider-settings get
  ib jerry provider-settings get --asiakas 1402
"
`;

exports[`Help snapshots — contract stability > help for ib jerry provider-settings set matches snapshot 1`] = `
"USAGE
  ib jerry provider-settings set [flags]

DESCRIPTION
  Upsert a provider company's BetoniJerry settings (PUT /api/jerry-provider-settings). Partial-payload-safe: only the body keys present are written (omit a key to preserve it). jerryPersonId must belong to the target company. --asiakas targets another company. Requires --reason.
  Permissions: requires edit-tier on the target company (tarjousAdmin / company admin).
  Timezone: dates interpreted in active company timezone (Europe/Helsinki).

FLAGS
  --body JSON    JSON: { jerryPersonId?, openingHours?, companyDescription?, maintainsOrderInfo? }
  --asiakas NUMBER    Target company asiakasId (default: your own)
  --reason STRING    Audit-log reason (REQUIRED)

WRITE-SAFETY FLAGS
  --dry-run            Validate without persisting. Returns the would-be response.
  --idempotency-key K  Replay protection. Cached for 24h.
  --reason TEXT        Free-text justification. Stored in audit log.

GLOBAL FLAGS
  --endpoint URL  --request-id ID  --quiet  --verbose  --pretty  --json

OUTPUT (JSON, stdout)
  { asiakasId } or { dryRun: true, wouldUpdate: {...} }

ERRORS (stderr, exit non-zero)
  400  Invalid field / contact not in company → check jerryPersonId belongs to the company
  403  No edit rights on company → use a tarjousAdmin/admin token for that company
  401  Token expired          → ib auth refresh
  500  Backend error          → retry with --verbose

EXAMPLES
  ib jerry provider-settings set --body '{"openingHours":"ma-pe 7-16","maintainsOrderInfo":true}' --reason "update opening hours"
  ib jerry provider-settings set --body '{"jerryPersonId":6233}' --asiakas 1402 --reason "set contact"
"
`;

exports[`Help snapshots — contract stability > help for ib jerry request get matches snapshot 1`] = `
"USAGE
  ib jerry request get [flags]

DESCRIPTION
  Get one pump request. Default is the customer-owned recap (GET /api/pumppuRequests/:id, scoped to the caller's personId). --provider returns the provider-facing detail (GET /api/pumppuRequests/:id/provider-detail, requires provider role) including your own offer + attachments; customer PII (lat/lng/phone/email) stays masked until your offer is accepted/confirmed.
  Permissions: requires --provider: provider company (isPumppuToimittaja).
  Timezone: dates interpreted in active company timezone (Europe/Helsinki).

FLAGS
  --requestId NUMBER    Positional — pumppuRequestId
  --provider BOOLEAN    Provider-facing detail view (provider role)

GLOBAL FLAGS
  --endpoint URL  --request-id ID  --quiet  --verbose  --pretty  --json

OUTPUT (JSON, stdout)
  default: { pumppuRequestId, status, asiakasId, maaraM3, osoite, lat, lng, ... } | --provider: { request:{...}, ownOffer:{...}|null, ownAttachments:[…], requestAttachments:[…], messageThreadId }

ERRORS (stderr, exit non-zero)
  404  Request not found / not yours → verify requestId (and that you own it, or use --provider)
  403  Not a provider (for --provider) → switch to a provider company
  401  Token expired          → ib auth refresh
  500  Backend error          → retry with --verbose

EXAMPLES
  ib jerry request get 4012
  ib jerry request get 4012 --provider
"
`;

exports[`Help snapshots — contract stability > help for ib jerry request list matches snapshot 1`] = `
"USAGE
  ib jerry request list [flags]

DESCRIPTION
  List BetoniJerry pump requests (tarjouspyynnöt). Default --mine returns the caller's own requests (GET /api/pumppuRequests/mine). --open returns the provider inbox of open requests (GET /api/pumppuRequests/open) and requires a provider company (isPumppuToimittaja); customer PII is masked there until your offer is accepted. --status (CSV) and --limit apply to --mine only.
  Permissions: requires --open: provider company (isPumppuToimittaja).
  Timezone: dates interpreted in active company timezone (Europe/Helsinki).

FLAGS
  --open BOOLEAN    Provider inbox of open requests (provider role)
  --mine BOOLEAN    Your own requests (default)
  --status STRING    Filter --mine by status (CSV: open,pending_verification,accepted,cancelled,expired,no_supply)
  --limit NUMBER    Max rows for --mine (server caps at 200) (default: 100)

GLOBAL FLAGS
  --endpoint URL  --request-id ID  --quiet  --verbose  --pretty  --json

OUTPUT (JSON, stdout)
  ListEnvelope<{ pumppuRequestId, status, createdAt, sentAt?, osoite, formattedAddress, totalM3|maaraM3, ... }> (fields differ between --mine and --open; --open is PII-masked)

ERRORS (stderr, exit non-zero)
  403  Not a provider (for --open) → switch to a provider company, or use --mine
  401  Token expired          → ib auth refresh
  500  Backend error          → retry with --verbose

EXAMPLES
  ib jerry request list
  ib jerry request list --open
  ib jerry request list --mine --status open,accepted --limit 50
"
`;

